		<title>20THE POW BURN 2</title>
		<content>     Recently, local farmers have      
 installed expensive underground       
 drainage networks and pumps which have
 greatly reduced the area and frequency
 of flooding.  This has resulted in the
 upgrading of farmland from pastoral to
 arable.                               
     However it is unlikely that the   
 basin will ever be completely free    
 from flooding because of;             
     1. the very gentle gradient, and  
     2. the{Pow Burn}drains in the     
 opposite direction to the River Earn  
 leading to a reversal of flow when the
 Earn is in flood.                     
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
